# Architecture Boundaries

## Integrated Next.js + Payload architecture

The app uses a **single Next.js application** with Payload CMS integrated inside it. This is NOT a separate backend вҖ” Payload runs as part of the same app.

### Route groups

When Payload is introduced, the app directory should be organized as:

```
app/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ (frontend)/          вҶҗ public website routes
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ [locale]/        вҶҗ locale-prefixed pages
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ page.tsx
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ our-work/
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ about/
в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ ...
в”ңв”Җв”Җ (payload)/           вҶҗ Payload admin panel routes
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ admin/
в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ [[...segments]]/
в”Ӯ           в””в”Җв”Җ page.tsx
в”ңв”Җв”Җ api/                 вҶҗ API routes (Payload REST, custom endpoints)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ layout.tsx           вҶҗ root layout
в”ңв”Җв”Җ robots.ts
в””в”Җв”Җ sitemap.ts
```

### Dependency direction

```
Frontend components вҶ’ Payload Local API / data layer вҶ’ Database
                   вҶҳ Shared types & utilities вҶҷ
```

- **Frontend** (`components/`, `app/(frontend)/`) may import from Payload data layer
- **Frontend** must NOT import Payload admin internals or Payload config directly in client components
- **Payload collections/globals/blocks** define the schema; they do not import frontend components
- **Shared** (`lib/`, types) can be used by both frontend and Payload

### Data access pattern

- **Server components** should fetch data via Payload Local API (`payload.find()`, `payload.findGlobal()`)
- **Never** call REST API from server components вҖ” use Local API
- REST API exists for external consumers or client-side mutations only
- Client components receive data as props from server component parents

### Collection / Global / Block organization

```
collections/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ Works.ts              вҶҗ work items (films, series, unscripted)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ TeamMembers.ts        вҶҗ team bios
в”ңв”Җв”Җ Media.ts              вҶҗ Payload media collection (images, files)
в”ңв”Җв”Җ News.ts               вҶҗ awards & news items
в””в”Җв”Җ ...

globals/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ SiteConfig.ts         вҶҗ branding, design tokens, SEO defaults
в”ңв”Җв”Җ Navigation.ts         вҶҗ header/footer nav structure
в”ңв”Җв”Җ ContactInfo.ts        вҶҗ contact details, social links
в””в”Җв”Җ ...

blocks/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ HeroBlock.ts          вҶҗ hero section config
в”ңв”Җв”Җ ContentBlock.ts       вҶҗ rich text section
в”ңв”Җв”Җ GalleryBlock.ts       вҶҗ media gallery
в””в”Җв”Җ ...
```

### What NOT to do
- Do not create a separate backend service or API server
- Do not use hexagonal / ports-and-adapters patterns (this is a CMS website, not a microservice)
- Do not introduce message queues, event buses, or event-driven patterns
- Do not create monorepo packages вҖ” keep everything in one app
- Do not abstract Payload behind repository interfaces вҖ” use Payload Local API directly
